HEADWORD: Reseat
<hw>Re*seat"</hw> <pr>(r?-s?t")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To seat or set again, as on a chair, throne, etc.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To put a new seat, or new seats, in; <as>as, to
<ex>reseat</ex> a theater; to <ex>reseat</ex> a chair or
trousers.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reseau</ent>⟦br⟧
